      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Song for the Pulaski, Though Not the Skyway</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>George Gamow letter on Joseph D'Agnese's June 25 article on New Jersey's covered bridges and lack of songs about Pulaski Skyway; notes Jimmy Sturr and Orchestra's 1991 album that includes tune entitled Pulaski Highway Polka (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I enjoyed Joseph D'Agnese's whimsical look at New Jersey's covered bridges (In Search Of, June 25), and I join him in lamenting the lack of ditties saluting our beloved Pulaski Skyway. However, I would like to draw Mr. D'Agnese's attention to the 1991 release, ''When It's Polka Time at Your House,'' by Jimmy Sturr and his Orchestra. It features a peppy little tune entitled ''The Pulaski Highway Polka.'' Sure, it's no Skyway, but if you squint at the song title, it's darn close.</p>
        <p>GEORGE GAMOW  Nutley</p>
      </block>
